# Storefront Rules â€” apps/storefront

These rules apply to every file you create or modify inside `apps/storefront/`.

---

## Stack Reference

| Concern | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 16, App Router |
| Language | TypeScript 5, strict mode |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 |
| i18n | next-intl |
| Class merging | `cn()` from `lib/cn.ts` |
| HTTP client | Medusa JS SDK via `lib/medusa-client.ts` |

---

## App Router Rules

- Root locale layout lives at `app/[locale]/layout.tsx`
- All public pages live under `app/[locale]/(storefront)/`
- Auth pages live under `app/[locale]/(auth)/` (Phase 5)
- Account pages live under `app/[locale]/(account)/` (Phase 5)
- API routes live under `app/api/` (no locale prefix)
- Loading states: `loading.tsx` file in the route segment
- Error states: `error.tsx` file (must be `"use client"`)
- 404: `not-found.tsx` at `app/[locale]/not-found.tsx`

### Server vs Client components

```
Default: Server Component (no directive needed)

Use "use client" ONLY when the component needs:
  - useState / useReducer
  - useEffect / useLayoutEffect
  - Browser APIs (window, document, navigator)
  - Event listeners
  - Third-party client-only libraries
```

Never put `"use client"` on a layout or page unless absolutely required.
Extract interactive parts into small leaf components instead.

---

## i18n Rules

- Every visible string must use `useTranslations()` (client) or `getTranslations()` (server)
- Never hardcode user-visible text in components
- Translation namespace matches the feature: `nav`, `home`, `product`, `cart`, `footer`, `common`
- Always add keys to BOTH `messages/ar.json` AND `messages/en.json` simultaneously
- Arabic (`ar`) is primary â€” write Arabic text first, then English

```tsx
// Server Component
import { getTranslations } from 'next-intl/server';
const t = await getTranslations('nav');

// Client Component
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';
const t = useTranslations('nav');
```

---

## RTL/LTR Rules

The `<html>` element has `lang` and `dir` set from the locale.
You must honour RTL in every component:

```tsx
// âś… Correct â€” logical properties flip automatically
className="ms-4 ps-3 rounded-s-md text-start"

// âťŚ Wrong â€” breaks RTL
className="ml-4 pl-3 rounded-l-md text-left"
```

Logical property mapping:
| Physical | Logical |
|---|---|
| `ml-*` | `ms-*` |
| `mr-*` | `me-*` |
| `pl-*` | `ps-*` |
| `pr-*` | `pe-*` |
| `left-*` | `start-*` |
| `right-*` | `end-*` |
| `text-left` | `text-start` |
| `text-right` | `text-end` |
| `rounded-l-*` | `rounded-s-*` |
| `rounded-r-*` | `rounded-e-*` |

---

## Layout System

- Use `Container` from `components/layout/Container.tsx` for all max-width wrapping
- Do not hard-code `max-w-7xl` or padding directly in pages â€” use Container
- Container already handles responsive padding (`px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`)

---

## Design Tokens

All colors use the `@theme` tokens defined in `app/globals.css`.
Use token names, not raw hex values:

```tsx
// âś… Correct
className="bg-brand text-text-inverse border-border"

// âťŚ Wrong â€” bypasses the token system
className="bg-[#1a1a2e] text-white border-gray-200"
```

Available token groups: `brand`, `accent`, `surface-*`, `text-*`, `border-*`, `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info`

---

## Component Rules

- Components go in `components/[feature]/ComponentName.tsx`
- Never exceed ~150 lines â€” split into sub-components if needed
- Props interface must be exported and named: `[ComponentName]Props`
- Use `React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLElement>` spread for passthrough props
- Always `cn()` for className â€” never string concatenation

---

## SEO Rules

Every public page must have `generateMetadata`:

```tsx
export async function generateMetadata({ params }: Props): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    title: 'Page title',          // will be templated: "Page title | Sama Link Store"
    description: 'Description',   // 120-160 chars
  };
}
```

- Use `title: { template: '%s | Sama Link Store' }` in the locale layout
- Set `metadataBase` in the root layout
- Every product page needs Open Graph image
- Every product page needs JSON-LD structured data (Phase 3)

---

## Performance Rules

- Use `next/image` for all product images â€” never `<img>`
- Always specify `width`/`height` or use `fill` with a sized container
- `priority` prop on above-the-fold images only
- ISR: `export const revalidate = 3600` on product/collection pages (Phase 3)
- Avoid importing heavy libraries in Server Components if they're client-only

---

## Medusa API Client Rules (Phase 2+)

- All API calls go through `lib/medusa-client.ts`
- No raw `fetch()` calls outside `lib/`
- All response types must be defined in `packages/types`
- Errors must be caught and handled â€” never let API errors crash the page silently

---

## Files That Must NEVER Be Modified by Cursor Without Explicit Approval

- `app/globals.css` â€” design token changes require Claude approval
- `app/[locale]/layout.tsx` â€” root layout changes require Claude approval
- `lib/cn.ts` â€” utility, do not change
- `lib/i18n.ts` â€” replaced by next-intl config, do not modify
- `tsconfig.json` â€” do not modify compiler options
- `next.config.ts` â€” only modify when a task explicitly requires it
- `tailwind.config.*` â€” Tailwind v4 uses CSS config only, no JS config needed
- `package.json` â€” only modify when a task explicitly requires adding a dependency
